column3: Apparently this requires Python 3.6, whereas we support Python 3.4 (held back for RHEL I guess)
Fixed, works with Python 3.4 now. Does anyone know if we have integration tests that use this?
> Fixed, works with Python 3.4 now. Does anyone know if we have integration tests that use this?\n\nI don't think so.

> Does anyone know if we have integration tests that use this?\n\nDo you mean that use rpcauth.py? Yes: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/d7b0258ff037ae90f60a86fc68cb55069c96e8d0/test/functional/rpc_users.py#L40
